"A broken laser walker.  No longer shall you hear the snap of superheated "
"air, smell the burning of flesh.  Still, you may be able to reclaim parts "
"from the wreck."
msgstr ""

#: .\walker_item.json
msgid "broken bootleg walker"
msgid_plural "broken bootleg walkers"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'broken bootleg walker'}
#: .\walker_item.json
msgid ""
"A broken bootleg walker.  Its guns are quiet now.  Still, you may be able to"
" reclaim parts from the wreck."
msgstr ""

#: .\walker_item.json
msgid "broken flare walker"
msgid_plural "broken flare walkers"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'broken flare walker'}
#: .\walker_item.json
msgid ""
"A broken flare walker.  Its flares shall remain dark, forevermore.  Still, "
"you may be able to reclaim parts from the wreck."
msgstr ""

#: .\walker_item.json
msgid "broken tesla walker"
msgid_plural "broken tesla walkers"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'broken tesla walker'}
#: .\walker_item.json
msgid ""
"A broken tesla walker.  The dance of lightning has ceased.  Still, you may "
"be able to reclaim parts from the wreck."
msgstr ""

#: .\walker_item.json
msgid "broken fusion walker"
msgid_plural "broken fusion walkers"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'broken fusion walker'}
#: .\walker_item.json
msgid ""
"A broken fusion walker.  City and forest need not fear its wrath any longer."
"  Still, you may be able to reclaim parts from the wreck."
msgstr ""

#: .\walker_item.json
msgid "broken buckshot walker"
msgid_plural "broken buckshot walkers"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'broken buckshot walker'}
#: .\walker_item.json
msgid ""
"A broken buckshot walker.  Deer and duck alike rejoice.  Still, you may be "
"able to reclaim parts from the wreck."
msgstr ""

#: .\walker_item.json
msgid "broken chicken walker"
msgid_plural "broken chicken walkers"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'broken chicken walker'}
#: .\walker_item.json
msgid ""
"A broken Northrup ATSV.  It lays quiet now, though looking upon it brings "
"memories of fire and death.  Still, you may be able to reclaim parts from "
"the wreck."
msgstr ""

#: .\walker_mon.json
msgid "chicken walker"
msgid_plural "chicken walkers"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'chicken walker'}
#: .\walker_mon.json
msgid ""
"The Northrop ATSV, a massive, heavily-armed and armored robot walking on a "
"pair of reverse-jointed legs.  Armed with a 40mm anti-vehicle grenade "
"launcher, 5.56 anti-personnel gun, and the ability to electrify itself "
"against attackers, it is an effective automated sentry, though production "
"was limited due to a legal dispute."
msgstr ""

#: .\walker_mon.json
msgid "scrap walker"
msgid_plural "scrap walkers"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'scrap walker'}
#: .\walker_mon.json
msgid ""
"The Northrup ATSV, a massive, heavily-armed and armored robot walking on a "
"pair of reverse-jointed legs.  Armed with a 40mm anti-vehicle grenade "
"launcher, 5.56 anti-personnel gun, and the ability to electrify itself "
"against attackers, it is an effective automated sentry.  Or would be, if it "
"wasn't held together with duct tape and hope."
msgstr ""

#: .\walker_mon.json
msgid "super walker"
msgid_plural "super walkers"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'super walker'}
#: .\walker_mon.json
msgid ""
"A large combat walker based on the Northrup ATSV.  Armed with an M2 Browning"
" .50 calibre machine gun, electroshock and -magnet units alongside six "
"mechadendrite-mounted blades.  Features  improved combat logic, thick "
"superalloy-ceramic composite plating, enhanced optics, motors and sensors "
"and an offensive defence system ."
msgstr ""

#: .\walker_mon.json
msgid "unarmed super walker"
msgid_plural "unarmed super walkers"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'unarmed super walker'}
#: .\walker_mon.json
msgid ""
"A large combat walker based on the Northrup ATSV.  Though it is armed with "
"electroshock and -magnet units alongside mechadendrite-mounted blades, you "
"really should deactivate it to install its primary weapon systems."
msgstr ""

#: .\walker_mon.json
msgid "unarmed walker"
msgid_plural "unarmed walkers"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'unarmed walker'}
#: .\walker_mon.json
msgid ""
"A Northrup ATSV cobbled together from scrap.  Armed with a only a tazer, it "
"is ineffective in combat, and really should be deactivated for weapon "
"installation."
msgstr ""

#: .\walker_mon.json
msgid "bootleg walker"
msgid_plural "bootleg walkers"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'bootleg walker'}
#: .\walker_mon.json
msgid ""
"A Northrup ATSV cobbled together from scrap.  Armed with a pair of 5.56 "
"rifles, it is quite deadly.  Still, you shouldn't expect the reliability and"
" resilience of the real thing."
msgstr ""

#: .\walker_mon.json
msgid "buckshot walker"
msgid_plural "buckshot walkers"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'buckshot walker'}
#: .\walker_mon.json
msgid ""
"A Northrup ATSV cobbled together from scrap.  Armed with a pair of automatic"
" shotguns, it is quite deadly.  Still, you shouldn't expect the reliability "
"and resilience of the real thing."
msgstr ""

#: .\walker_mon.json
msgid "flare walker"
msgid_plural "flare walkers"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'flare walker'}
#: .\walker_mon.json
msgid ""
"A Northrup ATSV cobbled together from scrap.  Equipped with a flaregun and "
"tazer, it functions as a spotter for more lethal models.  Still, you "
"shouldn't expect the reliability and resilience of the real thing."
msgstr ""

#: .\walker_mon.json
msgid "laser walker"
msgid_plural "laser walkers"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'laser walker'}
#: .\walker_mon.json
msgid ""
"A Northrup ATSV cobbled together from scrap.  Armed with a trio of lasers, "
"it is fairly deadly.  Still, you shouldn't expect the reliability and "
"resilience of the real thing."
msgstr ""

#: .\walker_mon.json
msgid "fusion walker"
msgid_plural "fusion walkers"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'fusion walker'}
#: .\walker_mon.json
